SurEau at Puechabon

INTRODUCTION

This is an R Markdown document showing a validationexercisse of SurEau-Ecos model at puechabon site during year 2017
1/ The model is parametrized for Quercus ilex
2/ The plant, soil and stand parameters are shown
3/ Validation data data including water potential and sapflow are loaded
4/ OUtputs plots are shown

1- Load the model and packages required

2- Load the access path

Three types of path have to been set and will be used later on to construct input parameters and options of the model
1/ climate data path : note that it is dayly climate data that are disagregated at the hourly time step by the model (well have a look later)
2/ Soil parameter path : includes soil and rock fraction content as well as pedotransfer parameter for the van Genuchten
model. this helps to compute the TAW, soil conductance and water potential of the different soil layers 3/ Vegetation parameters path that will permit to load all plant physioogical parameters (refer to the doc)
4/ outpout path that defines where the outputs files will be written 

# set paths
climateData_path          <- paste0(mainDir,'/projects/Puechabon_fit/Climat_Puechabon_site.csv')
soilParameters_path       <- paste0(mainDir,'/projects/Puechabon_fit/Soil_Puechabon.csv')
vegetationParameters_path <- paste0(mainDir,'/projects/Puechabon_fit/vegetation_Puechabon.csv')
output_path               <-  paste0(mainDir,'/projects/Puechabon_fit/test_Puechabon.csv')

3- Creating initialisatrion objects

The following lines of codes create options and inputs that will be used to run the model

3-1 Modelling options

these options set the way certain computation are done. Without going into details it tells the time step of internal computation of the hydraulic processes.
You can set the type of transpiration model you want to use (Jarvis is the a gs model).
You can define the shape of the function for transpiration regulation
You can define plenty of other things including if deflation due to caviation occurs or the the numerical scheme 

# Create input files and run SurEau-Ecos
modeling_options  <- create.modeling.options(compOptionsForEvapo = "Fast",
                                             transpirationModel = 'Jarvis',
                                             defoliation = T,
                                             stomatalRegFormulation = "Sigmoid") #PiecewiseLinear

3-2 Simulation parameters

This is where you define the parameters for the given simulation : Which years you want to run (must be consecutive if many)
The type of output files (if you want many detailed outputs at hourly time step or only a few daily or yearly outputs)
It requires the main directory and the output_path

simulation_parameters <- create.simulation.parameters(startYearSimulation = 2016,                       
                                                      endYearSimulation = 2018,
                                                      mainDir = mainDir,
                                                      outputType = 'diagnostic_subdaily',
                                                      overWrite = T,
                                                      outputPath = output_path)

3-3 Creating the Input object

This is where you create the object thhat will serve as input there are three folds: Climate data Soil parameters vegetation parameters stand parameters All this uses the path defined earlier expect the stand parameters that are set ahead They sometimes required the *modellingoptions or the simulation_parameters** to produce internal settings

stand_parameters      <- create.stand.parameters(LAImax =2.2, lat = 43.75, lon = 3.6)

climate_data          <- create.climate.data(filePath = climateData_path, 
                                             modeling_options = modeling_options,
                                             simulation_parameters = simulation_parameters) #

vegetation_parameters <- create.vegetation.parameters(filePath = vegetationParameters_path, 
                                                      stand_parameters = stand_parameters, 
                                                      soil_parameter = soil_parameters,
                                                      modeling_options = modeling_options)

3-4 Manual settings of some parameters

You can use the object previously defined to reset soma parameters manually. But take it does not work for all paramters. for instance resseting the point of stomatal closure at 12 or 88 % wont work because thhe model use other parameters computed internally during the creatin of the vegetation_parameters. If iy are not sure,, youd better change the parameter in the input file.

vegetation_parameters$gsMax = 220
vegetation_parameters$gCrown0 = 150
vegetation_parameters$gmin20 = .5
